  "prompt": "Septoplasty at fortis?",
  "response": "Fortis Healthcare is a reputable medical service provider with multiple facilities across India. If you're considering a septoplasty at Fortis, here are some steps and considerations to keep in mind:\n\n### Steps to Schedule a Septoplasty at Fortis:\n\n1. **Research and Choose a Fortis Location:**\n   Fortis has various hospitals in different cities. Choose the one that is most convenient for you.\n\n2. **Consultation:**\n   - **Book an Appointment:** You can typically book an appointment through the Fortis website or by calling their helpline.\n   - **Initial Consultation:** During your first visit, you will meet with an ENT (Ear, Nose, and Throat) specialist who will evaluate your condition and discuss whether septoplasty is the right option for you.\n\n3. **Pre-Operative Assessment:**\n   - If septoplasty is recommended, you will likely undergo some pre-operative tests, such as blood work or imaging studies, to ensure you are fit for surgery.\n\n4. **Surgery Planning:**\n   - The doctor will discuss the procedure, potential risks, and recovery time. You will also receive instructions on how to prepare for the surgery.\n\n5. **Surgery:**\n   - Septoplasty is usually performed under general or local anesthesia and can take about 30-90 minutes.\n\n6. **Post-Operative Care:**\n   - After the surgery, you will be given specific instructions on how to care for your nose, manage pain, and monitor for any complications. Follow-up appointments will be scheduled to monitor your recovery.\n\n### Considerations:\n\n- **Cost:** The cost of septoplasty can vary based on the facility, surgeon's fee, and other factors. It's a good idea to check with Fortis directly for an estimate.\n- **Insurance:** Check whether your health insurance covers septoplasty at Fortis.\n- **Recovery:** Plan for time off work or school for recovery, as you may need to rest and avoid strenuous activities.\n\n### Contact Information:\n\nTo get started, you can visit the Fortis Healthcare website ([www.fortishealthcare.com](https://www.fortishealthcare.com)) or call their customer service for more specific information and to book an appointment.\n\nBy following these steps, you can be well-prepared for your septoplasty procedure at Fortis.",
